      "type": "Claim",
      "name": "CFD model reliably identifies worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under CPB use",
      "description": "The CFD hemolysis model, exercised across five flow-speed combinations (2.5–5.0 L/min; 2000–3500 RPM), correctly ranks operating conditions by hemolysis severity and predicts a relative hemolysis index RH < 1 relative to the predicate device across all evaluated configurations. The model is therefore fit for purpose in supporting the regulatory decision that the proposed device tolerances do not introduce clinically significant increases in pump-induced hemolysis.",
      "scope": "FDA generic centrifugal blood pump geometry; Class II CPB indication; operating envelope 2.5–5.0 L/min, 2000–3500 RPM; blood viscosity 0.0035 Pa·s; haematocrit 35%."
